## 📂 Project Structure

```text
ipl-ml-project/
├── data/
│   ├── ipl_json/          # Raw Cricsheet JSON files (1,243 matches)
│   └── processed/         # Cleaned CSVs generated by notebooks
│       ├── matches.csv        # 1,243 matches, 64 feature columns
│       └── deliveries.csv     # 295,732 ball-by-ball deliveries
├── notebooks/
│   ├── 01_data_extraction.ipynb       # Raw JSON → Structured CSVs
│   ├── 02_feature_engineering.ipynb   # Phase runs, boundaries, dot% calculations
│   ├── 03_impact_player_analysis.ipynb # Deep dive into the 2023 rule change
│   ├── 04_additional_analysis.ipynb   # Venue/Team EDA & ML feature matrix creation
│   └── 05_modeling.ipynb              # 4 ML models training, validation & export
├── models/
│   ├── best_models.pkl        # Trained scikit-learn models
│   └── model_summary.json     # Performance tracking schema
├── website/                   # Vanilla web dashboard (No heavy backend required)
│   ├── index.html             # Impact player visual deep-dive
│   ├── stats.html             # Advanced player & venue stats
│   ├── model.html             # Interactive client-side match predictor
│   └── [assets]               # Shared dark-theme CSS & standalone Chart.js scripts
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
